description.narrative: 190/192 multitask community health workers were technically equipped to maintain service provision in COVID-19 context and in implementation of barrier measures. Through them, women and children are still receiving essential community-based health services in the Far-North and North regions. The training received by 118 health professionals and 122 CHW permitted 72 COVID-19 women have had safe delivery and others are enjoying an inch free pregnancy. Last but not the least, 180 preterm and low birth weight infants received kangaroo mother care in the 5 UNICEF-supported health districts in the East region. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/06/2020
